{"cursor":"37674","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n'Clothing' is fiber and textile material worn on the body. The wearing of\nclothing is mostly restricted to human beings and is a feature of nearly all\nhuman societies. The amount and type of clothing worn depends on physical,\nsocial and geographic considerations. Some clothing types can be gender-\nspecific, although this does not apply to cross dressers.\n\nPhysically, clothing serves many purposes: it can serve as protection from the\nelements, and can enhance safety during hazardous activities such as hiking and\ncooking. It protects the wearer from rough surfaces, rash-causing plants, insect\nbites, splinters, thorns and prickles by providing a barrier between the skin\nand the environment. Clothes can insulate against cold or hot conditions.\nFurther, they can provide a hygienic barrier, keeping infectious and toxic\nmaterials away from the body. Clothing also provides protection from harmful UV\nradiation.\n","linknr":997,"url":"Clothing","recorded":1362373184,"links":155,"instances":["microbiology","bible","island","theatre","genesis","clothing","biophysical","clothing","son_of_jacob","country","activewear","clothing","garment"],"pdf":["http://www.eva.mpg.de/genetics/pdf/Kittler.CurBiol.2003.pdf","http://www.eva.mpg.de/genetics/pdf/Kittler.CurBiol.2003.pdf","http://www.divreinavon.com/pdf/BegedSimlaJBQ.pdf","http://www.divreinavon.com/pdf/BegedSimlaJBQ.pdf","http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA283851&Location=U2&doc=GetTRDoc.pdf","http://www.dtic.mil/cgi-bin/GetTRDoc?AD=ADA283851&Location=U2&doc=GetTRDoc.pdf","http://www.eva.mpg.de/genetics/pdf/Kittler.CurBiol.2003.pdf"],"categories":["Clothing|"],"headings":["Origin of clothing","Functions","Scholarship","Cultural aspects","Origin and history","Contemporary clothing","Political issues","Life cycle","Gallery","See also","References","Further reading","External links",""],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/9/9